{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of trust by embezzling funds in their professional capacity as an accountant. While the amount of $25,000 and the violation of fiduciary duty warrant a period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and punishment, several mitigating factors are present. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has demonstrated a degree of remorse and responsibility by beginning the restitution process. The outburst from the courtroom spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing guidelines. A sentence of 12 months balances the seriousness of the white-collar crime with the defendant's clean history and efforts to repay the stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 12
}
